dct_description_sm: A sublayer from migration routes for the five largest refugee populations in modern US history. This layer focuses on Syrian Arab Republic refugee migrations to the top 10 destination countries during the course of the Syrian Civil War from 2012 to 2015.
Source data: “Population Statistics.” The UN Refugee Agency, http://popstats.unhcr.org/en/persons_of_concern. Accessed 7 June 2016.
